Privacy Policy for 8-bit Music Master

Effective Date: [Date, e.g., January 1, 2024]

I, xu ning ("I," "me," or "my"), built the 8-bit Music Master app as a paid application. This SERVICE is provided by me at the price listed on the App Store and is intended for use as is.

This page is used to inform users regarding my policies with the collection, use, and disclosure of Personal Information if anyone decides to use my Service.

If you choose to use my Service, then you agree to the collection and use of information in relation to this policy. The Personal Information that I collect is used for providing and improving the Service. I will not use or share your information with anyone except as described in this Privacy Policy.

Information Collection and Use

I value your privacy. I only collect data that is essential for the app to function properly or to improve the user experience.

What information is collected?

1. Automatically Collected Information (Crash Logs & Diagnostics)
The app may collect certain information automatically, including, but not limited to, the type of mobile device you use, your mobile device's unique ID, and diagnostic reports ("Crash Logs"). This data is anonymous and is used solely to fix bugs and improve app stability. This data is collected via [Name the tool, e.g., Apple's Crashlytics / Firebase].

2. Analytics Data
To understand how users interact with 8-bit Music Master, I use third-party analytics services (such as [e.g., Apple's built-in analytics, Mixpanel, or Flurry]). These tools collect anonymous data about which features are used most often and how you navigate the app. This helps me decide what to improve next.

3. Audio and Music Data
8-bit Music Master is a music creation tool. The app processes audio input and music sequences locally on your device. I do not collect, store, or have access to any music files, compositions, or audio recordings you create within the app. Your creations remain solely on your device unless you choose to export or share them via other services.

4. Purchase Information
Since 8-bit Music Master is a paid application, all payment transactions are processed exclusively by Apple through the App Store. I, xu ning, do not collect or have access to any of your financial information (such as credit card numbers or payment details). Please refer to Apple's privacy policy for information on how they handle your purchase data.

5. User-Provided Information (Select the options that apply to you, delete the rest)

Account Information: If 8-bit Music Master requires you to register, I may collect your name and email address. This is used only to manage your account.
Photos / Media: If the app accesses your photo library, it is only to allow you to save or load audio files or project files. I do not upload your media to any server without your explicit permission.
File Storage: The app may access your device's storage to save and load music projects and exported audio files. This access is used only for the core functionality of the app.
Third-Party Services

8-bit Music Master uses third-party services that may collect information used to identify you.

